Package registration

Class StudentCampRegisterer

  • Object
    • StudentCampRegisterer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRegisterCamp
    public class StudentCampRegisterer
extends Object
implements IRegisterCamp
    Represents an class that manages the registration database and allows clients to register for a camp as a camp attendee.
    Since:
    2023-11-17
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Soo Qi Yang, Teo Kai Xuan, Masagca Merwyn Louie Dumasis, Nguyen Phuong Linh, Tee Jeeng Yee

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      private IGetCampSlots campStudentSlotChecker
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if there are still available camp attendee slots in the camp.
      private IReduceCampSlots campStudentSlotReducer
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to reduce the remaining number of camp committee slots upon successful registration of the student as camp attendee.
      private ICheckCampVisibility campvisibilityChecker
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp is even visible to the student, to be allowed to register.
      private ICheckSchoolMatch checkSchoolMatch
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp's faculty is open to the student.
      private ICheckNoClash clashWithRegisteredChecker
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp that a student wants to register for clashes with his already registered camps.
      private IGetCampsRegistered registeredCampNamesGetter
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to obtain the list of camps a student has already registered for.
      private ICheckRegistrationClosed registrationClosedChecker
      An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp's registration deadline has passed.
      private RegistrationDataBase registrationDataBase
      This StudentCampRegisterer's associated registration database.

    • Constructor Detail

      • StudentCampRegisterer

        public StudentCampRegisterer​(RegistrationDataBase registrationDataBase,
                             IGetCampSlots campStudentSlotChecker,
                             IReduceCampSlots campStudentSlotReducer,
                             ICheckSchoolMatch checkSchoolMatch,
                             ICheckNoClash clashWithRegisteredChecker,
                             ICheckRegistrationClosed registrationClosedChecker,
                             RegisteredCampNamesGetter registeredCampNamesGetter,
                             ICheckCampVisibility campvisibilityChecker)
        Creates a new StudentCampRegisterer with its associated registration database and interfaces required to perform its method functions successfully. These interfaces are obtained from the CampDataBase and this constructor should automatically be called upon the creation of a RegistrationDataBase or if not, after using the static method from CRDBInterfaceInitialiser.
        Parameters:
        registrationDataBase - This StudentCampRegisterer's associated registration database.
        campStudentSlotChecker - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if there are still available camp attendee slots in the camp.
        campStudentSlotReducer - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp's faculty is open to the student.
        checkSchoolMatch - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp's faculty is open to the student.
        clashWithRegisteredChecker - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp that a student wants to register for clashes with his already registered camps.
        registrationClosedChecker - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp's registration deadline has passed.
        registeredCampNamesGetter - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to obtain the list of camps a student has already registered for.
        campvisibilityChecker - An interface used by StudentCampRegisterer to check if the camp is even visible to the student, to be allowed to register.

    • Method Detail

      • registerCamp

        public void registerCamp​(Student student,
                         String campName)
        Description copied from interface: IRegisterCamp
        Registers a student to a camp, given the student name and camp name. Upon failure, the class that implements this interface should print an error message and return. The class can also vary its implementation on the role it wants to assign to the student that is registering.
        Specified by:
        registerCamp in interface IRegisterCamp
        Parameters:
        student - Name of student to be registered to camp.
        campName - Name of camp that student should be registered to.
